Class InvTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component

    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public final class InvTree
extends javax.swing.JPanel
    InvTree - implements the GUI JPanel for a the tree view of inventory. * There should only be one instance of this object connected to a higher GUI. * In the case of the INV system it is made a tab. It is important that the * owning GUI contain a call to InvTree.exitCleanup() to insure that all * modified trees are written. * *This class implements popup menus which need access to other elements of *the graphic interface to work. See the constuctor doc * * @author D.C. Ketchum Oct 2003 *
    See Also:

      • itemTransfer

        public static boolean itemTransfer(int locID,
                                   java.sql.Timestamp effective,
                                   Item item)
        Transfer an Item onto a tree for display. The locID is used to find the right tree root (epic) and it is put on the level just below the tree root. Note : this presumes this is an inventory transaction - it must occur on newest treeroot on the location and always causes the treeroot to write so Inventory remains in sync with tree display
        Parameters:
        locID - A location ID to move this item to
        effective - The effective date of the transfer
        item - The item to put on the tree
        Returns:

      • itemTransfer

        public static boolean itemTransfer(TreeRoot tr,
                                   Item oldItem)
        Transfer an Item onto a tree for display. The locID is used to find the right tree root (epic) and it is put on the level just below the tree root. This routine cannot be used to transfer to the current epoch. It is an error for the tree root to be the newest treeroot!
        Parameters:
        tr - A TreeRoot to put this item on
        oldItem - The item to put on the tree
        Returns:
        true if the item was successfully transfered

      • itemSubstitution

        public static boolean itemSubstitution(int locID,
                                       java.sql.Timestamp eff,
                                       Item oldItem,
                                       Item newItem)
        If an item is substituted this routine should be called by the inventory oriented part of the system. This will determine if a new tree is needed, and build that tree. The idea is the inventory system just knows something was changed, but all knowledge and manipulation of the tree side and backing database is done here.
        1) Find the latest tree for this location, if this item is immutable skip to 3)
        2) find the "old" item on a current tree. If tree is more than 1 hour away from the effective date of substitution, clone a new tree at the substitution effective date.
        3) On the resulting tree from 1 and 2, substitute the item for the old Item. If oldItem != null and newItem == null, the old item is simply trimmed from the tree If oldItem == null and newItem != null, the new item is just hung on the root if oldItem != null and newITem != null, then newItem replaces oldItem on has nothe tree if they are the same equipment type. If not, oldItem is cut from tree, its children moved to root and new is added at root
        Parameters:
        locID - Location ID where substitution is to occur
        eff - Time at which this substitution is effective
        oldItem - Item currently at that location (if null this is a simple transfer)
        newItem - Item to be put in
        Returns:
        True if substitution is legal, false otherwise

      • rebuildTree

        public static void rebuildTree(TreeRoot tr)
        Rebuild the whole tree structure and expand the given tree root. This routine should not be needed, but for some reason when we modify the tree structure in various places, the GUI display does not match the structure of the DFTN. This forces this to be true by rebuilding from the data base.
        Parameters:
        tr - The tree root to expand
